article.headline: North Carolina 92, Hofstra 45
article.story:
CHAPEL HILL, N.C. (AP) -- Ivory Latta had 18 points and seven
assists to lead 14th-ranked North Carolina to a 92-45 victory
Sunday over Hofstra.

Latta made four 3-point baskets for the Tar Heels (2-0). They
led 41-19 at the break, then scored the first 27 points of the
second half.

Camille Little had 16 points and nine rebounds for North
Carolina, which got 14 points and 11 boards from Candace Sutton and
13 points from Nikita Bell. Cigi McCollin led Hofstra Pride (0-1)
with 16 points.

The Tar Heels shot 47 percent and the Pride 21 percent.
